settings.helpText: The path defines the position of the page in your website's architecture. E.g. "About" will make the page accessible at http://www.your-website.com/about/. Use "index" for your homepage. Use the "/" character for subpages, e.g. "about/me" and "about/my-company" will create 2 pages under the "about" page.
Specify page specific metadata. E.g. title and description. (you don't have to specify a canonical url)
Build your page by composing blocks.
A gallery of images to build your portfolio, photo albums, ...
